TY  - JOUR
AU  - Leach, J. Chris
AU  - Madhavan, Ananth N.
T1  - Price Experimentation and Security Market Structure
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/6.2.375
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
SP  - 375
EP  - 404
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine the role of market makers in facilitating price discovery. We show that a specialist may experiment with prices to induce more informative order flow. thereby expediting price discovery. Market makers in a multiple-dealer system, unlike a specialist system, do not have the incentives to perform such costly experiments because of free-rider problems. Consequently, the specialist system may provide open markets where competition fails but at the cost of wider bid-ask spreads. We analyze the effect of experimentation on the bid-ask spread and provide an exploratory analysis of intraday specialist data that is consistent with our price experimentation hypothesis.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/6.2.375
ER  - 



