TY  - JOUR
AU  - Heston, Steven L.
T1  - A Closed-Form Solution for Options with Stochastic Volatility with Applications to Bond and Currency Options
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/6.2.327
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
SP  - 327
EP  - 343
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - I use a new technique to derive a closed-form solution for the price of a European call option on an asset with stochastic volatility. The model allows arbitrary correlation between volatility and spot-asset returns. I introduce stochastic interest rates and show how to apply the model to bond options and foreign currency options. Simulations show that correlation between volatility and the spot asset's price is important for explaining return skewness and strike-price biases in the Black-Scholes (1973) model. The solution technique is based on characteristic functions and can be applied to other problems
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/6.2.327
ER  - 



